<p>Sensuality</p>

<p>Hereâ€™s a extract from George Orwellâ€™s essay, â€œInside the Whale.â€ Itâ€™s not a particularly exciting passage, certainly not one of Orwellâ€™s best. But note even in at his driest, Orwell makes regular appeals to the sensual, which I have bolded, below. Here, we dip into the piece just after Orwell has quoted from a pastoral poem, which is what â€œitâ€ refers to in the first sentence.</p>

<blockquote>
